"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue..md#Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue. One such example is the creation of a nanoporter (NP)-hydrogel for the locoregional in situ induction of CD133-specific CAR-MΦs in a glioblastoma resection cavity. This aids to deter  local recurrence of the brain tumour by stimulating an adaptive immune response to GSCs rather than systemic injection. [[Glioblastoma tumours generally recur within a narrow margin around the resected tumour cavity due to the presence of self-renewable glioma stem cells (GSCs).]] Thus it is important to eradicate them completely, especially those missed by surgical resection.{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/Local administration of CAR T-cells into the region of a solid tumour targets remaining tumourigenic cells and reduces adverse responses in healthy tissue..md#References":true},"mtime":1709479540563,"size":873,"hash":"bd656a90b778354b6076fa6fc1ac24a8aa5626913ea1b46e559167990b058d7b"}],"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.0033078,-0.01259162,-0.02186965,0.03866125,0.04509843,-0.00732089,0.01357048,-0.03335118,-0.01076437,-0.00328514,-0.00929926,-0.0